# Rust
/target
**/target
**/*.rs.bk
Cargo.lock.bak

# Fuzz outputs
fuzz/target
fuzz/corpus/*
!fuzz/corpus/seed/
fuzz/artifacts

# Reference codebases — large external repos cloned into references/ for study
# (Paperclip + Hermes). Not part of Relix; never tracked.
/references/paperclip/
/references/hermes-agent/

# Local secrets / keys (no secrets are ever committed; this is belt-and-braces)
*.key
*.pem
*.der
secrets/
.env
.env.*

# IDE / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# Reference material used during architecture analysis; not part of the project.
# See docs/architecture-overview.md for what was learned from these.
reference/

# Build artifacts from tools
*.profraw
*.profdata
coverage/

# Claude harness scratch
.claude/

# Demo state — created by scripts/alpha-bringup-m5.sh, never committed.
dev-data/
dev-keys/*.key
dev-keys/*.pub
dev-keys/*.aic
# Node identity bundles are minted locally at first boot (self-healing via
# `relix identity ensure`). Never commit pre-minted bundles — they carry a
# wall-clock expiry and are signed by a local org root that does not exist
# on a fresh checkout, so a committed bundle is broken/expired on arrival.
dev-keys/*.bundle

# Per-operator policy file. The shipped policy lives in
# configs/policies/dev.toml; `local.toml` is an operator's
# private tweak that should not enter the repo.
configs/policies/local.toml

# Bridge-owned secrets file (AI provider keys + Telegram bot
# token configured via the dashboard's settings pages). Written
# by the bridge at mode 0600 on POSIX. See
# docs/dashboard-redesign.md for the security model.
bridge-secrets.toml
**/bridge-secrets.toml
